%C A155038 Indexing the triangle from n=0 and k=0, T(n,k) is the number of binary words of length n that begin with a run of exactly k 0's. O.g.f.: 1/((1-y*x)*(1-x/(1-x))). - _Geoffrey Critzer_, Feb 15 2012
